definitions: To change from one side or party to another.
To suddenly feel a particular emotion or sensation.
To affect someone in a particular way, often unexpectedly.
To travel a short distance, especially across a body of water or a border.
examples: Why don't you come over for dinner tonight?
Many voters came over to the opposition party.
I don't know what came over me, but I just started laughing.
A strange feeling came over him as he entered the old house.
They came over from France for the weekend.
